      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "A statement attributed by the\nChronicle to Pres. Matt Comerford,\nnational president of the steam en-\ngineers union. concerning the at\ntitude of union men in politics, is\nresented by E. A. Cooney, secre-\ntary of the local union. He says\nall Comerford ever said about poll\ntics while here officially was that\nhe would never advise union men,\nbers to vote for man who had\ntried to cut their heads off, re-\nferring to Taft.\n\n\nComerford was quoted as a\nmember of the executive commit\ntee of the American Federation of\nLabor, whereas he has never held\nsuch Office."
    }
  ]
